Node.definition: = action by which humans supervise, direct or oversee work (such as building or repairing) or worship (such as singing or playing instruments)
= a type of song (שִׁיר) probably to be accompanied by musical instruments
= man; ◄ son of Jesse (יִשַׁי) ► king of Israel (יִשְׂרָאֵל)
= state in which someone refrains from speaking
= action by which humans express their appreciation, admiration, respect, and/or gratitude to deities about who they are and what they do
= mountain; ► that part of Jerusalem (יְרוּשָׁלַ͏ִם) on which the temple was built, also known as a fortress and stronghold, city of David (דָּוִד) YHWH's dwelling place
plural with singular meaning: = the highest God, creator of heaven and earth
= action by which humans make a solemn promise to a deity, ► which signals a commitment to perform a certain act or behave in a specific way, usually in return for a blessing from the deity
= action by which humans speak to a deity, often by raising their hands, ► requesting help or expressing their thankfulness
particle linking an event to a point in space; = relation indicating that event X ends at point in space Y
= living creature, including both humans and animals; ◄ conceived as an object that mainly consists of flesh; ≈ regarded as weak and passing
= a deed of deliberate wrongdoing resulting in a state of guilt which requires punishment
= process by which conditions greatly increase in intensity, to the extent that they appear to gain control over everything else, ≈ which can be either good or bad, depending on the condition
= action by which humans or groups defy an authority or a standard of behavior; by extension, can also refer to the punishment or guilt incurred from a trangression
= referent to a male participant that is addressed in a discourse
= action by which deities do not hold wrongdoers any longer responsible for certain actions, often as a result of an atonement ritual or a change in behavior of the guilty party
= state of being considered fortunate and blessed by God; ≈ accompanied by an attitude of admiration
= action by which someone makes a selection among several options, which include humans, divine beings, animals, other objects, or events
= causative action by which humans cause other humans or animals to move to a location relatively close to the location in focus
= area enclosed by walls or buildings

Node.gloss: to be satisfied (with something)|to have one's fill (of something)
Node.definition: literally: to be satiated (with an event); hence: = process by which humans become more than fully engaged in a certain process or activity, which can be either good or bad
= objects that are considered of a good quality and attractive to the eye

= construction surrounded by walls and covered with a roof; ◄ normally made of stones, wood, or clay; ► to be used as living quarters, for storage, as a prison, as a sanctuary, etc.; sometimes used to denote a smaller part of a large construction
= state in which people, objects and places have undergone the rituals that are required to make them fit to be in the presence of God or to be used in his service
= a building or set of buildings, distinguished from other constructions or houses by its magnificence ► and function, which is either religious or political
= state in which humans, deities, places and activities have qualities that inspire fear in others

= pattern of behavior of humans or deities that is in accordance to the requirements of the divine law and generally aimed at establishing or restoring this pattern as a standard, which in certain cases requires a victory over evil and results in prosperity and happiness
= action in which humans or deities respond to a question or situation, either by words or by actions
plural with singular meaning: = the highest God, creator of heaven and earth
= a state in which a human or deity helps a human in need to be safe / a safe state
= state in which humans live with confidence and without fear; ≈ often regarded as carelessness, especially when there is no mention of trust in YHWH

= the earth as opposed to the sky; sometimes used in a more specific sense to denote part of the earth, such as the dry land as opposed to the sea, or a specific region, area, country, or plot of land
= a large and deep body of water which collects in a depression of the land; containing either salt water or fresh water
= causative action by which humans or deities cause an object to be firmly located in a certain place
= a relatively high elevation of the earth’s surface; generally higher than a hill (גִּבְעָה)
= state in which humans, animals or deities have the ability to perform actions, or to prevail in, or endure situations that require the exertion or mustering of effort or force
= to wear a belt or girdle around one's waist
= the ability to accomplish great things because of characteristics, such as physical strength, power, bravery, skill, wealth, good character, or a combination thereof

Node.gloss: to hold back|to still|to calm|to control
Node.definition: = state in which humans or deities have the ability to keep things from happening or stop happening
= process by which turbulent waters produce a loud and intimidating noise
= a large and deep body of water which collects in a depression of the land; containing either salt water or fresh water
= process by which turbulent waters produce a loud and intimidating noise
= a ridge of water curling into an arched form between two depressions in open water
= action by which humans, animals, or objects produce a variety of sounds, sometimes associated with natural phenomena like heavy rain and the waves of a stormy sea
= a large body of people united by common descent, religion, or language

Node.gloss: to be afraid|to fear|to be in awe of|to revere
Node.definition: = state in which humans experience fear
= process by which humans make a certain place or area their home
= supernatural act of a deity, ◄ performed by the deity himself or in his name; ►in order to assert his power and greatness
= process by which an event starts from a certain place or position
= first half of the day, ranging from daybreak until noon; ≈ used figuratively to denote relief after a time of suffering, and associated with good as opposed to evil

= the time of day when the sun starts going down, when people leave their work and go home, have food, and go to sleep; this is also the time of the evening sacrifice, and the time when an unclean person who has gone through the cleansing rituals is declared clean, when fasting and mourning come to an end, and when the exposed body of an executed person needs to be removed

Node.gloss: to take notice|to be mindful (of someone, something)
Node.definition: = action by which deities or humans take notice of the misfortune or suffering of (other) humans, plants, or objects and intervene in order to help

= the earth as opposed to the sky; sometimes used in a more specific sense to denote part of the earth, such as the dry land as opposed to the sea, or a specific region, area, country, or plot of land
= process by which an event happens with great strength or intensity
= a relatively large quantity of liquid flowing with strength
plural with singular meaning: = the highest God, creator of heaven and earth
= state or process in which a certain location, container, or surface is filled or covered with so many objects that little or no space is left

Node.gloss: to prepare|to make ready|to make provisions (for something)
Node.definition: = causative action where humans or deities make objects ready for use
= seeds of cultivated cereal; ► used as food

Node.gloss: to prepare|to make ready|to make provisions (for something)
Node.definition: = causative action where humans or deities make objects ready for use
= long, narrow trench made in the soil by a plow
= a raised strip of earth or other material
= a brief and usually light fall of rain; ≈ regarded as a blessing
= causative process by which a relatively hard object is made softer

= process by which new growth comes up, either springing from the ground or from part of an existing plant, and starts growing; ≈ sometimes extended to denote the coming into existence of people, conditions, or activities

Node.gloss: to bless|to praise|to greet|to congratulate|to commend
Node.definition: = causative action by which deities grant a special favor to humans, objects, or events, or by which humans invoke a deity to do the same
literally: to crown; hence: = causative actions by which deities increase an event's importance by giving it certain qualities
= the impression left by a foot or shoe on the ground
= state in which the body of humans or animals contains a significant quantity of fat, ≈ which used to be regarded as the best part and associated with health and well being
= area not very suitable for sedentary life and agriculture because of its lack of water; suitable for grazing domestic animals and only inhabited by nomadic tribes and wild animals
mainly in poetical texts: = state in which humans feel and show great joy
= an elevation of the earth’s surface rising gradually and to a relatively small height from the surrounding level; generally lower than a mountain (הַר)

Node.gloss: to gird oneself|to put on (clothes, armor)
Node.definition: = action by which someone ties a belt or piece of cloth around the waist; hence also: to put on clothes or armor

Node.gloss: to be clothed > to be covered
Node.definition: = state in which objects are completely covered with a layer of other objects, such as plants, dirt, animals, ◄ as if it were a layer of clothing
= open land with enough grass and plants to graze cattle or flocks of sheep and goats

= group of small domestic animals traveling and feeding together; ◄ consisting of sheep and goats; ► hair or wool shorn for weaving into cloth; female milked for food; may be killed and eaten for meat; used as sacrificial animal; ≈ associated with large quantities and also with God's people, who are often seen as a flock with God as their shepherd
= state in which humans are covered with clothing
collective: = seeds of cultivated cereal; ► used as the main ingredient for bread and related food products; ≈ regarded as an essential condition for life

marker pointing to information that needs to be considered in addition to previous information (either explicit or implied), and also often used to affirm this new information as more conclusive or compelling than the information preceding it
= action by which one utters words with a set or improvised tune, whether accompanied by musical instruments and dancing or not
